abstract: Group of close associates demand access to Algerian Pres Abdelaziz Bouteflika, inflaming widespread speculation that ailing and sequestered man is no longer in charge of country; Bouteflika, who is 78, has suffered two strokes in recent years, leading to fears that his brother Said Bouteflika has initiated a soft coup; developments have attracted international concern as Algeria is oasis of relative stability in region.
lead_paragraph: After the president’s two strokes in recent years, his condition is so uncertain that a group of prominent associates has demanded to see him.

headline.main: Who Runs Algeria? Many Doubt It’s Ailing President Abdelaziz Bouteflika
headline.print_headline: Who Runs Algeria? Many Doubt It’s the President
